if you want to see them again.
Oh, no need!

4
00:00:49,930 --> 00:00:53,150
I'm sure everything was
done on the up and up.

5
00:00:53,250 --> 00:00:56,710
But let me tell
you something, cadet.

6
00:00:56,810 --> 00:00:59,630
In all my years
at this academy

7
00:00:59,730 --> 00:01:03,670
I have never had a student
who was more bull headed,

8
00:01:03,770 --> 00:01:07,190
more committed to avoid
learning at all costs.

9
00:01:07,290 --> 00:01:11,360
A cadet who's constant byword
was insubordination.

10
00:01:13,360 --> 00:01:16,960
Thank you, cadet.
What?

11
00:01:18,440 --> 00:01:22,190
Before you came to this academy
I was bored, uninspired,...

12
00:01:22,290 --> 00:01:24,790
..and this close to retiring.

13
00:01:24,890 --> 00:01:29,110
But your insolence and stupidity
have been the irritating grain

14
00:01:29,210 --> 00:01:34,870
of sand around which has formed
the pearl of my renaissance.

15
00:01:34,970 --> 00:01:39,000
I like me again. Cadet!

16
00:01:41,720 --> 00:01:44,510
As a thanks I
want you to have...

17
00:01:44,610 --> 00:01:47,080
..this.

18
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:55,350
Normally these are reserved for
cadets who have distinguished
themselves or whose parents

19
00:01:55,450 --> 00:02:00,630
have donated a building but you've
left your mark here in your own way.
So, what the heck!

20
00:02:00,730 --> 00:02:03,270
Wow! Sir,... this is great.

21
00:02:03,370 --> 00:02:08,510
Farewell, cadet.
Thank you so much.

22
00:02:08,610 --> 00:02:10,610
Careful that's razor...

