00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:59,990
Normally I dread the first day of
school. Mum's been on such a rampage
about Francis it's a relief be here.

32
00:03:00,090 --> 00:03:03,350
Thank God...

33
00:03:03,450 --> 00:03:06,270
..summer's... over.

34
00:03:06,370 --> 00:03:11,830
Hello, babies.
How's baby school, babies? Didn't
high school start a half hour ago?

35
00:03:11,930 --> 00:03:14,670
If I'm on time they'll
expect it every day.

36
00:03:14,770 --> 00:03:17,030
Ow! Ow! Ow!

37
00:03:17,130 --> 00:03:22,950
Hi, Reese. This is Gus. He's in the
lead to replace you as school bully.

38
00:03:23,050 --> 00:03:29,110
He gives a wedgie that'll knock your
socks off. I'm not just saying that
cos he's got me in a head lock.

39
00:03:29,210 --> 00:03:35,040
Grab your wrist and stave your
fingers. You'll get better leverage.
You listen to him. He's the man.

40
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:43,200
I've completed the research on our
new teacher if anyone's interested.

41
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:46,950
Lionel Herkabe.

42
00:03:47,050 --> 00:03:51,390
Born July 8th, 1963. Parents,
John and Ida. Notice anything?

43
00:03:51,490 --> 00:03:55,230
He was a Krelboyne. We
won't have to talk down to him.

44
00:03:55,330 --> 00:03:58,230
Finally, someone
who knows our pain.

45
00:03:58,330 --> 00:04:03,550
Bentley. Gifted High. Princeton.
Harvard Business. Why's he teaching?

46
00:04:03,650 --> 00:04:09,590
Well, there was some unpleasantness.
He quit a government think tank
to start a... dot.com.

47
00:04:09,690 --> 00:04:12,990
(ALL GROAN) One time
net worth 200 million.

48
00:04:13,090 --> 00:04:15,470
Now 137 dollars.

49
00:04:15,570 --> 00:04:19,960
(GASPS) Here he comes!
Here he comes!

50
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:54,070
Who's Dabney?
Me, sir. I took the liberty of
ordering you a decaf soy latte.

51
00:04:54,170 --> 00:04:59,870
Let me guess.
Emotionally needy. Closet bed-wetter.

52
