so you'll be seeking it from me.
Look elsewhere, son.

53
00:05:05,970 --> 00:05:09,230
Who's the anal-retentive outsider...

54
00:05:09,330 --> 00:05:12,830
..with repressed
matricidal tendencies?

55
00:05:12,930 --> 00:05:15,800
Yo, sir! Me, sir! Please, stop.

56
00:05:16,840 --> 00:05:20,630
As you may or may not know I was
once one of you, a Krelboyne.

57
00:05:20,730 --> 00:05:24,910
And I'm sure I would have made
the same lame attempt to ingratiate

58
00:05:25,010 --> 00:05:28,750
myself to the new soft-headed
thick-wit teaching my class.

59
00:05:28,850 --> 00:05:33,550
I've been there. I've been coddled
and preened. "Oh, you're a genius."

60
00:05:33,650 --> 00:05:37,630
"You can do anything you set your
mind to. It must be easy being you."

61
00:05:37,730 --> 00:05:40,470
Well, bull!
(ALL GASP)

62
00:05:40,570 --> 00:05:44,350
All that gets you is an ex-wife
and 14 million dollars in debt.

63
00:05:44,450 --> 00:05:48,910
I won't let you fall into the trap
society has set for you.

64
00:05:49,010 --> 00:05:52,910
Playtime is over, children!
You've had a free ride so far.

65
00:05:53,010 --> 00:05:58,310
It's time somebody challenged you,
tested your mental limits!

66
00:05:58,410 --> 00:06:04,670
I don't have a teaching certificate
from a two-year community college
like most of the people I said hello

67
00:06:04,770 --> 00:06:11,190
to this morning in the teachers
lounge but I'll muddle through with
my double doctorate from Harvard.

68
00:06:11,290 --> 00:06:14,510
This is a test!
Correct. You have 20 minutes.

69
00:06:14,610 --> 00:06:20,520
There are six essay questions.
I'm sorry, I thought this was
the gifted class. Begin!

70
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:39,030
Thanks for the ride. Are you sure
about this Alaska thing? Absolutely.

71
00:06:39,130 --> 00:06:43,990
I heard Alaska's a hole. Are
you kidding?
Cruise ships go there!

72
00:06:44,090 --> 00:06:48,270
For six weeks in the summer.
Isn't it dark the rest of the year?

73
00:06:48,370 --> 00:06:54,270
I don't have to justify myself
to you or anyone.
That's why I got emancipated, OK?

74
00:06:54,370 --> 00:06:58,350
OK. Good luck
with your parents.

75
00:06:58,450 --> 00:07:02,790
Well, they had a week to think about
it. Let's see how they take it.

76
00:07:02,890 --> 00:07:04,890
(DOOR SLAMS)

77
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:10,040
You...! You...!

78
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:16,200
You ungrateful son of a...

79
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:21,080
This wasn't meant to hurt you!

80
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:43,190
All I'm saying is you can get your
diploma first then do what you want.

81
00:07:43,290 --> 00:07:49,270
It's all about maximising your
options. Take in the long view.
(WINCES) Sorry about the closer.

82
00:07:49,370 --> 00:07:54,870
Nonsense. I wouldn't have taught you
if I didn't want you to use it.
What do I always say?

83
00:07:54,970 --> 00:07:58,350
The nards are fair game.
The nards are fair game!

84
00:07:58,450 --> 00:08:03,550
Sometimes you're presented with
an opportunity you can't pass up.
Understand?

85
00:08:03,650 --> 00:08:09,550
I'm not the one to worry about.
I know. I wanna get this straight
with mom. That's why I came here.

86
00:08:09,650 --> 00:08:12,440
OK, then. Honey!

87
00:08:14,440 --> 00:08:17,560
Your son has something
to say to you.

88
00:08:19,080 --> 00:08:23,240
Huh! I didn't know the
Henderson's painted their house.

89
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:27,360
(BELL RINGS)

90
00:08:31,520 --> 00:08:35,040
I have your test results.
You all got A's.

91
00:08:36,760 --> 00:08:40,830
But, since this is the gifted
class, I also factored in...

92
00:08:40,930 --> 00:08:46,440
..cogency of argument,
economy of language and penmanship,
which enabled me to do this.

93
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:51,950
What is that? A ranking board.
I thought you said we all got A's.

94
00:08:52,050 --> 00:08:57,030
Oh, you did. But some of you
got better A's than others.

95
00:08:57,130 --> 00:09:00,710
But we all still
have A's? Of course.

96
00:09:00,810 --> 00:09:04,430
So, er, what does being
number one get you? Nothing!

97
00:09:04,530 --> 00:09:07,950
Just the knowledge that
you are number one.

98
00:09:08,050 --> 00:09:10,960
Or that you are
not number one.

99
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:15,310
Yes, number five?
It's Dabney, sir.

100
00:09:15,410 --> 00:09:18,680
I know. What is it
number five? I forgot.

101
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:25,670
What... a jerk. Is that what
we're gonna turn out like?

102
00:09:25,770 --> 00:09:29,360
If I ever start acting like that
you have to promise to kill me.

103
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:33,710
No! No more death pacts.
Don't worry about it.

104
00:09:33,810 --> 00:09:39,590
The only way that stupid board can
have an effect on us is if we let it.
Those numbers mean nothing.

105
00:09:39,690 --> 00:09:42,750
What are... you doing?

106
00:09:42,850 --> 00:09:45,800
Nothing!
You were studying?

107
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:50,670
No, I wasn't. My book
just fell open at this page.

108
00:09:50,770 --> 00:09:54,110
You know... I'm
really not hungry.

109
00:09:54,210 --> 00:09:57,360
I think I left my recess
stuff in my locker.

110
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:04,990
My God! High school is awesome! They
have an entire room for detention.

111
00:10:05,090 --> 00:10:08,910
They put you in with juniors and
seniors. Some of them have records.

112
00:10:09,010 --> 00:10:11,390
It's really inspiring.

113
00:10:11,490 --> 00:10:13,910
What are you looking at?
Francis.

114
00:10:14,010 --> 00:10:17,870
He's still out there? Yeah, he's
eating out of the bird-feeder.

115
00:10:17,970 --> 00:10:21,990
Who's shoes are these? Who left
their shoes in the living-room?

116
00:10:22,090 --> 00:10:27,710
They're mine. Sorry. You're right,
you're sorry! Leaving your shoes
around like you don't care!

117
00:10:27,810 --> 00:10:32,990
I hope you like walking to school
in your socks! I said sorry.

118
00:10:33,090 --> 00:10:35,990
I've heard sorry before!
I don't think so.

119
00:10:36,090 --> 00:10:38,870
OK. I tell you
what we're gonna do.

120
00:10:38,970 --> 00:10:43,270
From now on when you wanna wear
shoes you check them out.

121
00:10:43,370 --> 00:10:47,040
Sign them in. Sign them out.
Just like a library.

122
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:50,990
Clean up those toys!

123
00:10:51,090 --> 00:10:54,040
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

124
00:11:03,480 --> 00:11:06,150
(PANTS) Oh! Oh, thanks.

125
00:11:06,250 --> 00:11:11,270
It's freezing. It's good
to see you. I've missed you.

126
00:11:11,370 --> 00:11:17,390
Ow! What's that for?!
Emancipation? What, you're
divorcing the family now?

127
00:11:17,490 --> 00:11:21,390
How could you do this to mom?
She left me no choice.

128
00:11:21,490 --> 00:11:26,270
Ow! We've done a lot of bad things
to mom but we've never abandoned her.

129
00:11:26,370 --> 00:11:31,070
I'm not abandoning her!
I'm just going to Alaska!
That's 5,000 miles away!

130
00:11:31,170 --> 00:11:36,910
It is not... 5,000 miles? Are you
serious? Oh, my God! It's gonna take
me forever to get up there!

131
00:11:37,010 --> 00:11:40,910
Then, don't go. Guys, I'm not doing
this to hurt anybody, I just...

132
00:11:41,010 --> 00:11:45,150
I really think this is my best
chance to make something of myself.

133
00:11:45,250 --> 00:11:49,670
Tell it to mom. I can't. She won't
talk to me. She's being so immature.

134
00:11:49,770 --> 00:11:53,670
In the meantime I'm stuck
outside in the freezing cold.

135
00:11:53,770 --> 00:11:57,640
Hey, would it be alright
if I slept in here tonight?

136
