228
00:22:35,560 --> 00:22:41,230
OK. I think we're ready to show
Principal Littledove what motivation
can accomplish.

229
00:22:41,330 --> 00:22:43,680
Well done, class.

230
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:55,040
You know, maybe we should just put
our heads down and take a rest for
a moment, shall we?

231
00:22:58,320 --> 00:23:03,910
Yes? Did you know I can count
to a million by prime numbers?

232
00:23:04,010 --> 00:23:07,310
I can, too!
So can I! It's easy!

233
00:23:07,410 --> 00:23:11,230
That's not necessary.
Two, three... Five, seven...

234
00:23:11,330 --> 00:23:13,710
11,...
13, 17, 19...

235
00:23:13,810 --> 00:23:15,810
23, 29, 31...

236
00:23:16,240 --> 00:23:19,950
Now by hundreds.
101, 211, 307...

237
00:23:20,050 --> 00:23:24,150
401.
503, 601...

238
00:23:24,250 --> 00:23:27,590
Seven! No!

239
00:23:27,690 --> 00:23:32,440
That is enough!
5,000, 1,009, 2,003...

240
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:37,440
2,023.
No!

241
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:43,350
Where are you going, number three?
It's hot! It's hot and I'm stupid!

242
00:23:43,450 --> 00:23:45,760
I'm stupid, too!

243
00:23:46,840 --> 00:23:49,430
Everybody please remain seated!

244
00:23:49,530 --> 00:23:52,120
(SCREAMS HYSTERICALLY)

245
00:24:06,160 --> 00:24:12,950
I'm nothing!
I'm invisible!

246
00:24:13,050 --> 00:24:16,830
(WHISTLES) Boy, that's quite
a show for your first week here.

247
00:24:16,930 --> 00:24:20,030
You were right.
You can't beat the system.

248
00:24:20,130 --> 00:24:23,000
But you sure can break it.

249
00:24:26,880 --> 00:24:30,630
I love you guys. I'll write
you when I get there, OK?

250
00:24:30,730 --> 00:24:36,630
Someday when you come back and
you're unemployed
and have no place to live,...

251
00:24:36,730 --> 00:24:39,830
..you can come
stay at my castle.

252
00:24:39,930 --> 00:24:42,160
Thanks, bud.

253
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:49,390
He's leaving. He just wants to
talk to you. Just hear him out.

254
00:24:49,490 --> 00:24:52,470
Lois! This has got to stop!

255
00:24:52,570 --> 00:24:57,200
He's going very far away and you're
not gonna see him for a long time.

256
00:24:58,600 --> 00:25:03,230
Honey, there are moments in life
that you just don't get back...

257
00:25:03,330 --> 00:25:08,680
..and I know you. If you do not deal
with this now it will haunt you for
ever.

258
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:15,670
Fine.

259
00:25:15,770 --> 00:25:19,280
I've lost a son
but gained a baby.

260
00:25:22,080 --> 00:25:24,310
I tried.

261
00:25:24,410 --> 00:25:26,440
I know.

262
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:34,830
Are you sure this
is what you want?

263
00:25:34,930 --> 00:25:37,120
Well, it better be.

264
00:25:39,920 --> 00:25:41,920
< Francis.

265
00:25:51,640 --> 00:25:54,080
I'm listening.

266
00:25:56,640 --> 00:26:00,070
This is what you get
for the way you treated me!

267
00:26:00,170 --> 00:26:03,950
I'm going to Alaska and
you'll be left without a son!

268
00:26:04,050 --> 00:26:09,190
And the way you treated me is
now a matter of public record!
I treated you?!

269
00:26:09,290 --> 00:26:13,150
I've sacrificed for you and you've
caused us nothing but pain!

270
00:26:13,250 --> 00:26:18,470
You want pain? I've got your scars,
baby! Three years in that school -
We went without for that school!

271
00:26:18,570 --> 00:26:24,470
Oh! Maybe I should thank you?
Thank you for making my life hell!

272
00:26:24,570 --> 00:26:29,550
Living hell? You've been a problem
since you were born! I'm outta here!

